    </div>
    <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
      <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-amber-900/50 border border-amber-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-amber-300 font-bold">2</span>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">You say "Hold" to pause them from drawing new tiles</p>
    </div>
    <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
      <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-amber-900/50 border border-amber-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-amber-300 font-bold">3</span>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">Announce "Challenge" — the word is looked up by a director or adjudication device</p>
    </div>
    <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
      <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-amber-900/50 border border-amber-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-amber-300 font-bold">4</span>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">Once opponent draws tiles, the challenge window closes — the word stands</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">When to Challenge</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
    <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Good Times to Challenge</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">High-scoring plays you've never seen before, words using unusual letter combos, plays in crucial endgame moments, words that "look wrong" despite familiar roots.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
    <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✗ Bad Times to Challenge</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Short common words (2-3 letters), words you half-recognise, when you're ahead comfortably, low-scoring plays that don't change the game outcome.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">The Art of Bluffing (Phoney Plays)</h2>

<p>Playing a non-word intentionally — known as a "phoney" — is a legal and common tactic in competitive Scrabble. If unchallenged, the word stays on the board and scores normally.</p>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Confidence sells:</span> Place your phoney quickly and confidently. Hesitation signals uncertainty and invites challenges. Top players practice their poker face for phoney plays.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Use plausible phoneys:</span> Words that look like they could be real (familiar prefixes + suffixes) are much harder to challenge than completely random letter strings.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Risk calculation:</span> Under NASPA rules, a successful phoney on a 40-point play effectively gives you a 65+ point swing (your 40 gained + opponent's lost turn). Under WESPA, the risk is lower because challenges are free.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Challenge Etiquette</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Be polite:</span> Say "I'd like to challenge" calmly. Never slam the table or accuse your opponent of cheating. Challenges are a normal part of the game.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Don't fish for information:</span> Asking "Is that really a word?" before deciding to challenge is considered poor etiquette. Either challenge or accept the play.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Accept results gracefully:</span> Whether your challenge succeeds or fails, move on without commentary. Dwelling on challenges disrupts the flow and your opponent's concentration.</p>
  </div>
</div>

